ORGANISERS of the Bloody Scotland Crime Writing Festival announced their most successful year yet after issuing 5661 tickets over three days. Crime fest makes a killing ORGANISERS of the Bloody Scotland Crime Writing Festival announced their most successful year yet after issuing 5661 tickets over three days.More than 60 authors attended, including Scottish stars Denise Mina, Christopher Brookmyre and Louise Welsh.Events took place in a number of historic venues across Stirling from Friday. 